ts\",\"content\":\"<ul>\\n<li>Add keyboard shortcuts - like alt-A go to index...etc.<\\/li>\\n<li>Shift click on list to select more items<\\/li>\\n<li>Pages list drag and drop<\\/li>\\n<li>JLM compression<\\/li>\\n<li>File manager folders<\\/li>\\n<li>Ability to add favourite post\\/pages to sidebar under All Pages for quick access<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<p><img src=\\\"\\/wildflower\\/img\\/thumb\\/The_night_is_coming-1400x1050.jpg\\/120\\/120\\/1\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" \\/><\\/p>\"}}',6,'2009-01-05 16:58:20'),(206,'wildpost',46,'{\"WildPost\":{\"title\":\"New post - add some comments\"}}',1,'2009-01-05 20:37:40'),(207,'wildpost',46,'{\"WildPost\":[]}',2,'2009-01-05 20:37:47'),(208,'wildpost',46,'{\"WildPost\":{\"title\":\"New post - add some comments\",\"content\":\"\"}}',3,'2009-01-05 20:37:59'),(209,'wildpost',46,'{\"WildPost\":{\"title\":\"About Cake\'s counter cache\",\"content\":\"<p>This function helps you cache the count of related data. Instead of counting the records manually via find(\'count\'), the model itself tracks any addition\\/deleting towards the associated $hasMany model and increases\\/decreases a dedicated integer field within the parent model table.<\\/p>\\n<p>The name of the field consists of the singular model name followed by a underscore and the word \\\"count\\\".<\\/p>\\n<p>Let\'s say you have a model called \\\"ImageAlbum\\\" and a model called \\\"Image\\\", you would add an INT-field to the \\\"image_album\\\" table and name it \\\"image_count\\\". Or if your names are more complex, here is another example: With \\\"BlogEntry\\\" and \\\"BlogEntryComment\\\", the name of the field would be \\\"blog_entry_comment_count\\\" and needs to be added to \\\"blog_entries\\\".<\\/p>\\n<p>Once you have added the counter field you are good to activate this functionality by adding the \\\"counterCache\\\" key to the \\\"$belongsTo\\\" association array and set the value to \\\"true\\\".<\\/p>\"}}',4,'2009-01-05 20:39:02'),(210,'wildpost',19,'{\"WildPost\